monster.plot.monsterAnalysis

monster.plot.monsterAnalysis.Rd

plots the sum of squares of off diagonal mass (differential TF Involvement)

monster.plot.monsterAnalysis(x, ...)

Arguments

x

an object of class "monsterAnalysis"
...

further arguments passed to or from other methods.

Value

Plot of the dTFI for each TF against null distribution

Examples

# \donttest{
data(yeast)
monsterRes <- monster(yeast$exp.ko,c(rep(1,42),rep(0,49),rep(NA,15)),
yeast$motif, nullPerms=10, numMaxCores=4)
#> Error: expr is not a data frame or expr is not a matrix or class(expr) not equal to "ExpressionSet"
plot(monsterRes)
#> Error in as.double(y): cannot coerce type 'S4' to vector of type 'double'
# }
